National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and Republic of Korea (ROK) National Security Advisor Suh Hoon met to discuss the importance of the U.S.-ROK alliance in maintaining peace and security in northeast Asia and the broader Indo-Pacific region. They emphasized the need for the complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and called on the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) to engage in serious and sustained diplomacy. Sullivan also expressed support for inter-Korean dialogue and cooperation. The two advisors recognized the progress made in strengthening the U.S.-ROK relationship and committed to further cooperation in areas such as advanced technology, secure 5G, resilient supply chains, and global health.